<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7a35e596-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s8211"><num value="8211">§ 8211.</num><heading> Nonapplicability of Federal Advisory Committee Act</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Chapter 10 of title 5 (commonly known as the “Federal Advisory Committee Act”), shall not apply to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a35e597-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s8211/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the Board; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id7a35e598-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s8211/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> any Partnership.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id7a35e599-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/116/188/tII/s211">Pub. L. 116–188, title II, § 211</ref>, <date date="2020-10-30">Oct. 30, 2020</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/134/937">134 Stat. 937</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/118/198/tII/s207">Pub. L. 118–198, title II, § 207</ref>, <date date="2024-12-23">Dec. 23, 2024</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/138/2683">138 Stat. 2683</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id7a35e59a-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id7a35e59b-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="id7a35e59c-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">2024—<ref href="/us/pl/118/198">Pub. L. 118–198</ref> substituted “Chapter 10 of title 5 (commonly known as the ‘Federal Advisory Committee Act’),” for “The Federal Advisory Committee Act (5 U.S.C. App.)” in introductory provisions.</p>
</note>
